<br>
Flamethrower states that the Orion would be feasible based on its design and its support from Von Braun and the funding from NASA. Orion was killed only due to the space treaty. He presents some information on Orions specs.<br>
<br>
Maddad refutes the statements based on the nuclear devices destroying the pusher plate and eventually Orion due to tens of millions of degrees of temperature from the nukes. He states that NASA pulled the plug because they and Von Braun realized Orion would never work.<br>
<br>
I could not find much information about Orion on the web, but what I found did not state one way or another whether Orion would work or not.<br>
<br>
I would like to hear unbiased informed opinions and hopefully some solid facts as to whether this bird would fly or not and whether or not the nukes present the problems which are discussed in the thread. I am not convinced either way.<br>
<br>
Flamethrower placed a link to this site (thats how I found it)so as to get Maddad to present his views here, but he refused and stated that anyone here would be welcome to join their discussion.<br>
<br>
Thanks - Q<br>
